active listening to help a student If your student is having difficulty in class, one strategy that may help is active listening. Active listening means paying close attention to what the student is saying and trying to understand their perspective. It also involves responding in a way that shows that you are listening and that you care. Some ways to do this include making eye contact, nodding, and saying things like "I see" or "I understand." Clinton's policy on Russian economy Hillary Clinton has not released a detailed policy on Russian economy. However, she has said that she will "stand up to Putin" and that she will "impose tough sanctions on Russia" for its actions in Ukraine.

Bill Clinton's policy on Russian economy Clinton's policy on Russian economy was to encourage free market reforms and privatization. He believed that this would lead to increased economic growth and development in Russia. Clinton also supported the admission of Russia into the G7, which was eventually accomplished in 1997.
